summary: An Ordinance providing for the improvement of Eighth Avenue Northeast, in the City of Seattle, from East Fifty-fifth Street to East Sixty-fifth Street, by grading and curing the same, in accordance with Resolution No. 471 of the City Council of the City of Seattle, and providing for the payment therefor by the mode of "Payment by Bonds," as provided by the laws of the State of Washington and the Charter and Ordinances of the City of Seattle
